workflow.name: Job brief analysis with OpenAI to find relevant templates and log in Google Sheets
workflow.description:
## Who‚Äôs it for

Recruiters, freelancers, and ops teams who scan job briefs and want quick, relevant n8n template suggestions, saved in a Google Sheet for tracking.

## What it does

Parses any job text, extracts exactly 5 search keywords, queries the n8n template library, and appends the matched templates (ID, name, description, author) to Google Sheets, including the canonical template URL.

## How it works
	1. Trigger receives a message or paste-in job brief.
	2. LLM agent returns 5 concise search terms (JSON).
	3. For each keyword, an HTTP request searches the n8n templates API.
	4. Results are split and written to Google Sheets; the workflow builds the public URL from ID+slug.

## Set up
	1. Add credentials for OpenAI (or swap the LLM node to your provider).
	2. Create a Google Sheet with columns: Template ID, Name, User, Description, URL.
	3. In the ‚öôÔ∏è Config node, set: GOOGLE_SHEETS_DOC_ID, GOOGLE_SHEET_NAME, N8N_TEMPLATES_API_URL.

## Requirements
	‚Ä¢ n8n (cloud or self-hosted)
	‚Ä¢ OpenAI (or alternative LLM) credentials
	‚Ä¢ Google Sheets OAuth credentials

## Customize
	‚Ä¢ Change the model/system prompt to tailor keyword extraction.
	‚Ä¢ Swap Google Sheets for Airtable/Notion.
	‚Ä¢ Extend filters (e.g., only AI/CRM templates) before writing rows.

options.systemMessage:
You are a helpful assistant. 
Extract exactly 5 distinct search keywords or short phrases from the following job description. 
Return them strictly as a JSON object with the keys "keyword1", "keyword2", "keyword3", "keyword4", "keyword5". 
Do not include explanations or extra text. 
The values must be concise search-ready terms taken directly from the job description context.

parameters.content:
Title: Setup Instructions
Content:
  - Add OpenAI credentials to the LLM node.
  - Add Google Sheets OAuth credentials to Sheets nodes.
  - Set GOOGLE_SHEETS_DOC_ID, GOOGLE_SHEET_NAME, and N8N_TEMPLATES_API_URL in ‚öôÔ∏è Config.
  - Create columns: Template ID, Name, User, Description, URL in your Google Sheet.

Title: Input Trigger
Content:
- This node starts the workflow when a chat message is received.
- The message should contain a job brief or description.

Title: Keyword Extraction
Content:
- The agent extracts 5 distinct keywords from the job description using OpenAI.
- Output is parsed and converted into an array for further processing.

Title: Template Search
Content:
- For each keyword, the workflow searches the n8n template library API.
- Results are split and processed individually.

Title: Google Sheets Logging
Content:
- Appends template search results to Google Sheets.
- Builds a public URL for each template and updates the corresponding row.

Title: General Notes
Content:
- No hardcoded API keys in HTTP nodes.
- You can swap Google Sheets for Airtable/Notion if needed.
- Ensure all required columns exist in your destination sheet.
